Hi Niti,

Yes, the commandline will output links only one hop away.
Heritrix does not use PageRank therefore we don&#39;t have that info as part of Heritrix reports. 
However, crawl.log has information that you need but it will require some work. Take a look at 
hoppath.pl -- that might give you some ideas on how to approach this problem.

For example:
$HERITRIX_HOME/bin/hoppath.pl crawl.log http://www.nyrock.com/images/jr_thumb.gif

2004-11-30-23-31-36 - http://www.nyrock.com/movies/200cigs.htm
2004-11-30-23-31-34  P http://www.nyrock.com/robots.txt
2004-11-30-23-31-49   R http://www.nyrock.com/
2004-11-30-23-46-54    L http://www.nyrock.com/gallery/index.asp
2004-12-01-01-37-13     L http://www.nyrock.com/gallery2.htm
2004-12-01-01-37-19      E http://www.nyrock.com/images/jr_thumb.gif

Let us know if we can help more.

Take care,
i.

P.S. It is great that you are comparing Heritrix against other crawlers. We will like to learn more 
about you findings.


